<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yaminye</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">IF you're someone who strongly believes that a Cleric shouldn't gank dwarves, please ignore this post  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR>No flames please, everyone has the right to play the way they see fit.<P>Okay, here is the situation:<BR>At 39th level the dock lady in Butcher Blok and I do not see eye to eye.  Seems as if she is friends with that evil Delin..go figure.<P>I would like to take the boat to the new lands, but am just a little shy of being able to take out the dwarves by the dock solo.  I don't melee dwarves, only use spells because they hit so hard and I miss so much that it ends up being a waste of my time.<P>I do have an idea, tho.  What if I aggro'd the dwarf, moved it to a far corner or even out by the guards, rooted it and atoned it.<BR>Could this work?<P>Any idea how long I should expect the dwarf to stay there before returning to its original spot? <P>Otherwise I know I can get someone to camo me and hope for the best, but would really like to have an alternative in case the camo pops.<P>Thanks,<P>Yaminye Eos<BR>39th Cleric<BR>Bristlebane Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Not sure on the time period of how long the atone lasts.  I assume eventually the NPC will move back to it's spot.  You will probably have to atone the NPC several times to get it to stick.<P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>52nd Dwarven Vicar<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">bellsong</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">yam.....<P>are you an evil cleric? if so ....flames would be uncalled for</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Juul</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Usually, as soon as root wears off, the atoned NPC will start pathing back to it's spot (assuming it is static).  You need to atone 2x to be safe, it doesn't always work the first cast.<P>What I would do (if I was KoS to dorfs) is wait until I see the shuttles at the dock, then just run and get on them.  NPCs, even if they are already pissed at you, can't usually hurt you once you are on a boat.  To be extra safe, you could pull her down and atone her, then get on the boat - but it isn't safe to sit there visible on the docks.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Morrun</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't know about the dwarves (never having attacked them), but I've used the root/atone trick to split the piranha pit in Kedge (2 piranhas spawn there - pulling both is bad news unless you have a large strong group, or someone who can charm/mez).<P>(For info: root one, wait for the other to attack you, someone taunts the mobile one away, atone the rooted one and return to the camp - south or east room).<P>I've found that the rooted & atoned fish tends to go home within a few seconds of the root wearing off.  You'd probably need to pull the dwarf to the far end of Butcherblock if you don't want her coming back before the boat arrives.<P>I guess you could repeat the process until the boat does arrive, sounds a bit of a pain though.  How about staying just out of aggro range until the boat arrives, then hitting the dwarf with a pacify and running past?  Just a thought.<P>------------------<BR>Morrun Catspaw<BR>Halfling Cleric (46th)<BR>Albion - Death Before Dishonour!<BR>Cazic-Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Suriya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yipes, no, atone will make the mob forget you, but they will go right back to their spawn place when root breaks.  <P>What I have always done, being a DE cleric, is wait somewhere safe, like on the other side of the wall...or even in the water, watching for the boat.  Then when the boat comes I just swim up into it.  Or ONTO it, if you are talking about the barges.<P>You can swim right INTO the boat, just line yourself up in front of it while it is parked at the dock, hit your page up key and swim forward right into the front of the boat.  It will usually swim you right INSIDE the boat, I've done it a million times.<P><P>------------------<BR>Suriya N`ytShaide<BR>Priestess InkyBlop of Innoruuk<BR>Clan of Shadows<BR>Founder of Clerics With Whips =P<BR>Tarew Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yaminye</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Great idea about swiming onto the shuttles! I've swam into the boat before, shulle shouldn't be that bad.   I'll check with some guildies about how many dwarves I'm kos to on the docks (thought there were two but could be wrong.)<P>Am I evil?<BR>Actually I'm a HE Cleric, but I roleplay Yami.  Long story (which we're writing out) but she gave half her soul to a soulless DE Necro love interest and received half his void.  Bottom line:  She has little conscience, but is still a nice gal  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>hehe<P>Yaminye Eos<BR>39th Cleric itching for 40<BR>Bristlebane Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dorad</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yaminye<P>You killed my beloved dwarven kinsmen!Felwithe will fell the Wrath of Brell for your treachery  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>Dorad Clericus </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nikushimi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Watch out for the little guy who shows up by the hanging fish at the dock ramp, too.<P>The female on the dock is indiff to me (Dark Elf), but this other guy ruined my last Unrest visit.  Not sure what his spawn cycle or faction is, but he probably hates ya as well!  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zirak</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am fairly certain that getting on a shuttle to take advantage of poor pathing AI is considered an exploit. Since so many people are already sensitive about guard killers, using this tactic is a /petition waiting to happen. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sheri</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This works!<P>First, always carry invisi potions with you. (buy them at any potion vendor).<P>Second, stand at the dock for Fi Vie in the corner. (as you look down the dock at Magnus, on your left is the corner safe from her and the fisherman)<P>Third, just watch the very first shuttle on the left.  When it starts to pull out, you have enough time to "invisi" with potion, run up the dock ramp and jump onto the last shuttle on the right.<P>Last, wave goodbye to Magnus and stick your tongue out as you ride safely past her invisible!<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
